  <data name="ModeDesc0" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Launch multiple games in parallel for a set duration.
Steam counts hours for all simultaneously (up to 32 games).
The simplest mode for quickly accumulating hours.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ModeDesc1" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Games are launched strictly one at a time.
Each runs for the specified duration, then automatically
switches to the next game in the list.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ModeDesc2" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Cyclic rotation in batches.
A batch of games is launched, after a set interval
it switches to the next batch, cycling through all.
Ideal for cycling through hundreds of games in one session.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ModeDesc3" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Accumulate target hours in batches (up to 32 games at a time).
When the current batch reaches the target time,
the next batch is automatically launched.
Continues until all games reach the target hours.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ModeDesc4" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Idle only within a specified time window.
Games automatically start and stop on schedule
(e.g., only at night from 23:00 to 07:00).</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ModeDesc5" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Periodic process restart for detection evasion.
Every N minutes all processes are killed and
restarted, simulating natural activity patterns.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="DetailedInfo0" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>🎮 Simple — Parallel Idle

The simplest mode. Launches the selected number of games
simultaneously. Steam sees them as running and accumulates
play time for each of them.

• Max 32 games simultaneously (Steam limitation)
• Set a time limit or run indefinitely
• All games start and stop together

Recommended for quickly accumulating hours across several games.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="DetailedInfo1" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>📋 Sequential — One by One

Launches games strictly one at a time. When one game
has run for the specified duration, it closes and
the next one from the list starts automatically.

• One game at a time
• Set hours per game
• Processes the entire displayed game list

Recommended when you need to accumulate many hours
in specific games sequentially.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="DetailedInfo2" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>🔄 Round-Robin — Rotation

Cyclic rotation in batches. The first batch of games
(up to 32) is launched, after the set interval it stops
and the next batch starts. When all batches are done,
the cycle starts over.

• Rotation interval is configurable (5-1440 min)
• Each batch — up to 32 games
• Runs indefinitely or for a set time

Ideal for cycling through hundreds of games in one session,
distributing hours evenly.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="DetailedInfo3" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>🎯 Target Hours — Until Target

Launches a batch of games (up to 32 simultaneously) and runs
for the specified number of hours. When time is up,
the current batch stops and the next batch starts.
Continues until all games in the list reach target hours.

• Batches of N games (configurable, max 32)
• Automatic batch switching
• Single-pass: each game is processed once

Recommended for mass hour accumulation across all games.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="DetailedInfo4" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>🕐 Schedule — Time Window

Idle runs only within a specified time window.
Outside the schedule, processes are automatically paused,
and resumed when the window starts.

• Set start and end time (HH:MM)
• Supports overnight windows (e.g., 23:00 — 07:00)
• Number of games and hours are configurable

Recommended for unattended idle (overnight, when away from PC).</value>
  </data>
  <data name="DetailedInfo5" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>🛡 Anti-Idle — Detection Evasion

Periodic restart of all processes.
Every N minutes all idle processes are killed
and restarted. This simulates natural behavior
(launching/exiting games).

• Restart interval is configurable (10-1440 min)
• Runs indefinitely or for a set time
• Creates a more natural activity pattern

Recommended for extended idle sessions (12+ hours).</value>
  </data>
